{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:13:08.185760+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Answer: **pnpm is required; npm is not acceptable.**\n\nHere is the justification from the repository:\n\n### 1. `package.json` — `\"preinstall\": \"npx only-allow pnpm\"`\nThe `scripts` section contains a **preinstall hook** that runs [`only-allow`](https://github.com/nicojs/only-allow) with the argument `pnpm`. This hook executes **before every `npm install` or `pnpm install`** and **throws an error if the package manager is anything other than pnpm** (including npm and yarn). This is a hard enforcement mechanism — it literally prevents `npm install` from completing.\n\n### 2. `package.json` — `\"packageManager\": \"pnpm@10.20.0\"`\nThe `packageManager` field (an [official Node.js/corepack convention](https://nodejs.org/api/packages.html#packagemanager)) pins the project to a specific pnpm version. Tools that respect this field (e.g., Corepack) will automatically use pnpm.\n\n### 3. Lock file: `pnpm-lock.yaml`\nThe repository ships a **pnpm lockfile** (207 KB), not a `package-lock.json` (npm) or `yarn.lock`. This is what all CI/CD and contributor workflows should use for reproducible installs.\n\n### 4. CI workflow (`.github/workflows/release.yml`)\nThe GitHub Actions workflow explicitly installs pnpm via `pnpm/action-setup@v4` and uses `pnpm install`, `pnpm run lint-fix`, `pnpm run test:unit`, and `pnpm run build`. There is no npm usage anywhere in CI.\n\n### 5. `README.md`\nAll project-setup instructions use `pnpm` commands (`pnpm install`, `pnpm run dev`, etc.). The one exception — `npm run lint-fix` under \"Lints and fixes files\" — appears to be a **documentation typo**, since every other command and the entire toolchain is pnpm-based.\n\n### Conclusion\nContributors are **expected (and enforced) to use pnpm**. Using `npm install` will fail at the `preinstall` hook. npm is **not** acceptable as a package manager for this project.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 533, "prompt_tokens": 6181, "total_tokens": 6714, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 58, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 5568, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007504098, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002866998, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00046371}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863177-vSABs3OeyliOfzQlULgq", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b7-9205-77e1-b45b-1c9a8508d4e3-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 6181, "output_tokens": 533, "total_tokens": 6714, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 5568}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 58}}}}]}}}
